node.text: Photo by @veronika_k_ko / I took this macro shot with a mobile phone at my neighborhood flower shop. I like to observe and enjoy flowers, communicating with them and capturing their beauty during their short lives. Especially in the summer, they are among my favorite subjects for photography. They are included in my photo series, Summer Vibes. I hope this beautiful flower can charge you positively! #YourShotPhotographer #flower #summer #fineartphotography #nature

node.text: Photo by @gabmejia / Witnessing this couple with matching jackets enjoy their time watching the sunrise at about 4,000 meters (13,000 feet) high on the tallest mountain in Taiwan was one of the loveliest sights I've seen. Indeed, love transcends even the tallest mountains. #YourShotPhotographer

node.text: Photo by Matt Hage @HagePhoto / Autumn has taken hold in the far north. Mountains near the Arctic Circle, the Brooks and Alaska Ranges, are either cloaked in brilliant fall colors or the white of their first snowfalls. Resident critters, from ground squirrels to caribou, are getting ready for six months of winter. #YourShotPhotographer

node.text: Photo by @Nadia.Aly.Photo / This is the largest species of hammerhead shark, the great hammerhead. They are often quite easy to see in the winter months off the coast of Bimini, Bahamas. During their time in Bimini, the normal count on sharks sits around 30 animals. What makes me sad is that these same animals head over to New York and Florida, where they are often caught for sport fishing. Did you know that humans kill over 100 million sharks every single year? #scubadiving #underwater #diving #snorkeling #YourShotPhotographer

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Your Shot on August 30, 2021. May be an image of sky, lightning and nature.

node.text: Photo by Michael Seeley @mseeley20 / At 3:14 a.m. ET on August 29, the CRS-23 mission launched from historic LC-39A at NASA's Kennedy Space Center, carrying 4,800 pounds (2,177 kilograms) of experiments, supplies, and hardware for the International Space Station. A SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket lifted a cargo Dragon capsule to orbit bound for rendezvous with the ISS the next day. This was the view from the NASA Press Site about three miles (five kilometers) from the pad, seen in a 202-second exposure.

Photo by @irina_sigl_photography / This is the little Fatima Chapel on a cold winter day in Upper Bavaria. I liked the pure white of the fresh snow in contrast with the pattern of the clouds in the blue sky.
Nikon Z7, 24mm, f/11, 1/640s, ISO 200. #YourShotPhotographer #Bavaria
